<br>
One thing that's a huge pain is that you can only sell loot to vendors who deal in that type of equipment. For instance, only hammer salesmen will buy hammers. Also, equipment has durability, and it can eventually get destroyed if you don't keep it repaired. It also is kind of a built-in anti-PL feature. At level 12, I went with a bunch of mid 20's to 30's to a camp. The idea was for me to just sit around and do nothing but soak in exp. Occasionally, that worked, but every now and then I'd get runt aggro. My groupies managed to keep me alive for th emost part, but I finally got chewed up by a giant alligator. When I respawned, I was just about totally naked. My low level armor wasn't able to withstand high level attacks.<br>
<br>
When you're naked in this game, I mean REALLY naked. I looked like a greek statue with a tiny weewee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub48.ezboard.com/bfatesforge.showUserPublicProfile?gid=clawfury>Clawfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Experienced</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/19/03 2:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub48.ezboard.com/ffatesforgefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=197.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Heh</span><hr size=1> GOGO statues! <p>______________________<br>
